  "text": "Damage occurring during flowering is difficult to recover for the crops due to the short length of the phenological stage and because of the plant physiology itself. Several studies have highlighted the relation between damage to flowers and yield reduction [CITATION_1] . Flowering is sensitive to low and high temperatures that could reduce flower fertility [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Intense rainy events could physically damage the flowers, while constant rains could reduce pollination. At the same time, the elements that threaten crop during the previous stages are still a menace and are taken into consideration. ASB 4. : grain filling (from BBCH growth stage 7 to BBCH growth stage 8).",
